f=Governance/board/custom/strategic-veto/SKILL.md · in=strategic-veto tests proposals against business's *locked strategic commitments* deliberate bets operator committed defined period ("we focused segment year," "no new ventures until ships," "the platform stays single-market until Q4") vetoes proposals materially conflict, citing commitment verbatim logging appeal path. mid-layer gate between constitution (near-immutable never-do's) config thresholds (tunable numbers): commitments change deliberately strategy cycles, until they're changed, they're enforced. · p=expensive drift business isn't breaking rules it's series individually-reasonable decisions quietly walk away strategy everyone agreed to. one passes budget check violates constitution article; together they mean year's focus never happened. skill gives board authority say "this conflicts what locked veto, here's appeal path," strategy changes happen deliberately through marcus operator, never accumulation. · wu=Triggers: "veto check," "strategy conflict," "does fit our strategy," automatically board's gate sequence after constitution-enforcement, whenever proposal commits resources direction. for: judging whether strategy itself good (marcus's strategy-advisor decision-critic territory), blocking things commitments simply don't cover commitment point means veto, improvised one. · st:/ Protocol=`Load locked commitments (configured path) \· -> If none exist: STOP — offer assets/locked-commitments-template.md; no veto power without a written strategy \· -> Identify which commitments the proposal touches \· -> Test for material conflict (quote the commitment, name the conflicting element) \· -> Rule: NO CONFLICT / VETO / TENSION (non-material — flag, don't block)` · h3:Phase 1 — Load=Read locked-commitments document board's config (`locked_commitments_path`). unset missing, stop: report locked commitments exist, offer template, make clear board **no veto power until operator locks strategy writing** veto based remembered inferred strategy exactly drift skill exists prevent. · h3:Phase 2 — Scope=List which commitments proposal plausibly touches why; state which don't apply. Shown output silent skips enforcement holes. · h3:Phase Test Material Conflict=touched commitment, quote verbatim apply scope test (each commitment template carries one). materiality bar: proposal **redirects resources, attention, positioning away commitment** merely "isn't about" it. Findings: · h3:Phase Test Material Conflict=**NO CONFLICT** proposal commitment coexist., **VETO** material conflict. Cite commitment ID, verbatim text, specific conflicting element proposal, commitment's expiry/review date veto "not while commitment stands," never permanent judgment idea)., **TENSION** real non-material friction (e.g., partial attention dilution). Flagged operator reasoning; block. · h3:Phase Appeal Path=VETO ships appeal path, always shape: **(a)** proposer ask operator amend retire commitment through strategy process (marcus operator board amend commitments itself), **(b)** re-scope proposal remove conflicting element resubmit. veto log records which path (if any) taken outcome. · h3:Phase 5 — Log=Record ruling proposal, commitments tested, finding, appeal path, outcome configured decision log. Veto history precedent: repeated vetoes against commitment signal either persistent drift pressure commitment longer fits, worth surfacing marcus next strategy review. · of=`## Strategic Veto Review: [proposal, one line] \·  \· **Commitments document:** [file/version/date loaded] \·  \· ### Commitments Touched` · pr=**No written commitments, veto power.** Board never vetoes remembered, inferred, "obvious" strategy., **Quote, don't paraphrase.** rule constitution-enforcement paraphrase interpretation drift., **A veto time-bound.** cites commitment expiry/review date; permanent ruling idea's merit., **Every veto carries appeal path.** veto without path amend re-scope wall, governance., **No conflict means veto.** Gaps commitments operator's fill, board's improvise around., **Repeated vetoes signal, success.** Surface pattern marcus either drift pressure real commitment stale. · f=Commitments path unset file missing stop Phase offer template., Commitments exist vague ("focus growth") still test, flag findings interpretation untestable language recommend operator tighten them template's scope-test structure., Proposal vague test ask specific resource/direction commitment it, rather ruling summary., Decision log unset deliver ruling operator directly say so. · b:with Other board Skills=Runs **after** constitution-enforcement (categorical rules first), alongside/before fiduciary-guard: proposal clear budget arithmetic still vetoed strategy conflict checks independent., constitution-enforcement owns near-immutable never-do's; skill owns deliberately-locked, expiring strategy bets. "commitment" meant hold years regardless strategy, belongs constitution., Boundary marcus: marcus (with operator) *sets amends* locked commitments (okr-cascade, strategy-advisor, decision-critic); board *enforces* them. Appeal path (a) routes there., risk-assessment-matrix pre-mortem evaluate proposals survived gate vetoed proposal doesn't consume further review.